<br>
::Standing up quickly, she tries to make her way back to Tartarus but can't, due to Hades' spell:: Damn it! ::Running out of the palace, Persephone mounts Demeter's manificent brown horse and begins a brisk quick ride to Olympus. As soon as she gets there, she literally jumps off the horse not even waiting to be escorted off. Running into the throne room she looks around for her fellow deities:: Someone help! ::Looking at the empty room, she runs into the meeting chamber. Seeing nothing but a few servants cleaning, she yells at them:: Where are the other gods and goddesses? Where is my father?!::The servant nervously shrug:: N-none of them are here dear mistress.. Everyone is gone doing who knows what...<br>
<br>
::Persephone sucks in her breath in frusteration:: Well find them and tell them that the souls of the dead have overrun the Underworld and that Hades, and the dark gods are in need of immediate aide! Go now! ::The servants bow quickly and scurry off. Persephone stands in front of a war hero's tapestry saying to herself:: Those servants won't find the other gods in time...Thanatos and Eris need help, and my poor Hades...If only I could.. ::Persephone stops talking while staring blankly at the tapestry:: <br>
<br>
::As fast as she came, Persephone runs back out to the courtyard and quickly mounts the horse. Leaving as quickly as she came, Persephone makes a hard, fast race for Sparta. After a half an hour, she arrives at the remains of a bloody, fierce battle. Persephone recalled Hades and the dark gods speaking of an upcoming battle and the awaited toll of new souls to arrive. While eating her food, she would hear them speak of who would be in Tartarus and whom would go to the Elysian Fields. Looking around at the lifeless bodies, she quickly finds the Spartan leader on the ground, holding his sword tightly to his dying heart. The leader looks up as the goddess with the radiating aura comes to him, gently kneeling while placing his head in her soft lap (sort of like Arwen in the Lord of the Rings flick when she first met Frodo ).<br>
<br>
Shh..Do not speak soldier...for you have fought hard and brave and will have your rightful place in the Elysian Fields..But there is one more battle there you will have to complete. My husband, your Lord Hades, as well as the rest of the Underworld, lie in great peril for the souls of Tartarus are free. You must find Thanatos and tell the heroes of the Elysian Fields to fight so they may put an end to our dilemma...please... ::The leader stares into her with misty eyes and coughs up blood through his mouth while barely speaking:: Yes my lady...my queen...::With moist eyes, Persephone leans down gently kissing his parched bloody lips as his soul departs for the Elysian Fields. Now all she could do was sit and wait:: <p>*~* Persephone...Queen of the Underworld.. faithful wife to Hades... princesss goddess of the Spring*~*</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goddesseris>Goddess Eris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Evil & Naughty</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/6/03 3:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/thephantomqueen/images/eristales.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unleashed</span><hr size=1> ::: Eris returned in a flash with hundred's of her minions, with swords, bows and arrows in hand, they began to fight there way to Thanatos and his castle stronghold. Some of her minions fell, but they could easily be replaced.<br>
