<br>
::He nodded as Thanatos and Cerberus returned from within the pit, while watching the surge of Thanatos' energies fly about the room.::<br>
<br>
::Upon return, Cerberus resumed his place beside Hades, standing guard to the body. Hades then shook his head and pointed to the next room, where Persephone lay down. Cerberus then did as Hades silently commanded, he went into the Throne room and sat beside Persephone, standing guard over her sleeping form::<br>
<br>
::Hades then looked at Thanatos and motioned for him to come closer::<br>
<br>
~Have you any clue as to whom is causing this disturbance? The only people I could think of POWERFUL enough to pull something such as this off, would be gods of the other realms, but even still, I reign supreme here and they would not be able to compete in my home realm, nor would they truly have a reason to. The only other thing I could think of...would be the combined might of the Titans. But they are locked in a sealed Cave. Hephaestus himself put the lock over that door and No one, not even the mighty Hades in his own realm; nor even Zeus himself could break that lock. Perhaps their magicks somehow seep through?~<br>
<br>
::The shade-like Hades shook his head and looked at his empty body:: ~That is my theory, how about yours, Old Friend?~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFF33>- </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite>Amazons Unite</a><font color=#FFFF33> - </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23>The Olympian Gods</a> <font color=#FFFF33> - </font><a href="http://pub163.ezboard.com/bmythicalodysseyforum">Home</a><font color=#FFFF33> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard</a> Ver. 7.3m<br>Copyright 1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

